<br>
 Here is how sneak pull works : you have two or more mobs at the same spot that can't be pulled single directly but that don't see through sneak, and you have enough room to throw something at them from long range. You turn sneak/hide on, wait for it to refresh, then throw a long range weapon at one of the mobs and just after pressing the range attack hotkey you press the hide/sneak one (with hide first). If you had enough range, you become hidden before the ranged attack hits your target. Thus, the mob comes single.<br>
<br>
 The exact same thing can probably done with our bolts (scars of sigil comes to mind) and someone else invising us.<br>
scars of sigil is 4.5 casting time while invis is 5.0 casting time. So you get at max range of your target. You cast scars of sigil and your partner casts invis on you at the exact same time (or max one sec later). Provided you had no fizzle problems, you should get a single pull.<br>
<br>
 Where to use this? Outdoor camps come to mind, like the bulthar one in CB, or the suits of sentient armor ones in WL, that can't be pulled single unless 58+ I think, and that both don't see through invis.<br>
 If u have not the right people at disposal to break those camps, this is a technique that seems quite viable. I'll t est as soon as I get the occasion (not really soon alas, I think..) and will report the results.<br>
<br>
 Any ameliorations that you could think of are very welcome. Anyone knows the casting time on Invis and Itu potions btw? I never had the opportunity or need to use them so far hehe =).<br>
<br>
<br>
